# Environment Variables Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and update values for your environment.

## Local Development

```
# MongoDB Configuration
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/grassroots_qr

# Flask Configuration
FLASK_HOST=127.0.0.1
FLASK_PORT=5000
FLASK_DEBUG=True

# Security
SECRET_KEY=dev-secret-key-change-in-production
```

## MongoDB Atlas (Cloud)

```
# Use your MongoDB Atlas connection string
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/grassroots_qr?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Other settings same as above
FLASK_HOST=0.0.0.0
FLASK_PORT=5000
FLASK_DEBUG=False
SECRET_KEY=your-production-secret-key
```

## Production Deployment

```
# MongoDB Production
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://prod_user:strong_password@prod-cluster.mongodb.net/grassroots_qr

# Flask Production
FLASK_HOST=0.0.0.0
FLASK_PORT=5000
FLASK_DEBUG=False

# Security
SECRET_KEY=generate-a-strong-random-key-here
```

### Generate a Strong Secret Key

```python
import secrets
print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))
```

Then paste the output as `SECRET_KEY`.
